1.Given an array arr[ ] of n positive integers, the task is to find the greatest element on the left of every element in the array which is strictly smaller than itself, if this element does not exist for an index print "-1".
Platform : GeeksforGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Complete {

    // Function for finding maximum and value pair
    public static int[] Smallestonleft(int arr[], int n) {
        int a[]=new int[n];
        TreeSet<Integer>t=new TreeSet<>();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            Integer sm=t.lower(arr[i]);
            if(sm==null) a[i]=-1;
            else a[i]=sm;
        t.add(arr[i]);
      }  return a;
    }
}

