2.Given an array A[] of length N. For each index, i (1<=i<=N), find the difference between the number of distinct elements in the left and right side in the of the current element in the array. 
Platform : GeeksforGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public static ArrayList<Integer> getDistinctDifference(int N, int[] A) {
         int arr[]=new int[N];
         HashSet<Integer>set=new HashSet<>();
         for(int i=0;i<N;i++){
             arr[i]=set.size();
             set.add(A[i]);
         }
         set.clear();
          int ar[]=new int[N];
          for(int i=N-1;i>=0;i--){
             ar[i]=set.size();
             set.add(A[i]);
         }
         ArrayList<Integer> ans=new ArrayList<>();
         for(int i=0;i<N;i++){
      ans.add(arr[i]-ar[i]);}
         return ans;
    }
}

Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/distinct-difference--170647/1
3.You are given a string s, which contains stars *.

In one operation, you can:

Choose a star in s.
Remove the closest non-star character to its left, as well as remove the star itself.
Return the string after all stars have been removed.
Platform : Leetcode
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public String removeStars(String s) {
        Stack<Character> st = new Stack<>();

        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (ch == '*') {
                st.pop();
            } else {
                st.push(ch);
            }
        }

        StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
        for (char ch : st) {
            ans.append(ch);
        }

        return ans.toString();
    }
}
Link : https://leetcode.com/problems/removing-stars-from-a-string/?envType=study-plan-v2&envId=leetcode-75